      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so if the micro-level simulations are showing that it actually accelerates concentration, does that mean the \"trickle-down\" thing from the DSGE models is basically just outdated or doesn't work in the real world? like, are those models actually still considered reliable for predicting this kind of thing?",
