      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The discrepancy suggests that the assumptions underpinning traditional DSGE models may not fully capture real-world distributional dynamics, particularly regarding capital returns versus labor income. While DSGE models are powerful for aggregate macro projections, their reliance on simplified labor-capital models often fails to adequately represent wealth accumulation at the highest deciles. Therefore, the micro-level simulations, which focus on specific household behavior, are currently providing a more nuanced and arguably more empirically grounded view on rising inequality.",
      "source": "target",
